        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer151361133" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer360720138704818087">&quot;Violence, homosexuality and the spiritual emptiness of post-war Japan: these were Mishima&apos;s key themes. But not all of these nine stories (and one play) exemplify them; for there was also a streak of wry, ironic humour. Here, then, is truly compelling reading. There is shock, explosion, illumination. Here is Mishima. Here is Japan.&quot;<br/><br/>That&apos;s the boast on tha back of my 1971 Penguin edition, and it&apos;s true!<br/><br/>I&apos;m usually not a fan of characters taking themselves too seriously, so I&apos;m not sure why I don</span>
  <span id="freeText360720138704818087" style="display:none">"Violence, homosexuality and the spiritual emptiness of post-war Japan: these were Mishima's key themes. But not all of these nine stories (and one play) exemplify them; for there was also a streak of wry, ironic humour. Here, then, is truly compelling reading. There is shock, explosion, illumination. Here is Mishima. Here is Japan."<br /><br />That's the boast on tha back of my 1971 Penguin edition, and it's true!<br /><br />I'm usually not a fan of characters taking themselves too seriously, so I'm not sure why I don't hate the couple in "Patriotism". I think it's probably because they're also really sexy.</span>
