<div id="review_3292505016" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3292505016" />
    <a title="Jimmy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3357765-jimmy"><img alt="Jimmy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1586258471p2/3357765.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3292505016?book_show_action=true">Apr 22, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jimmy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jimmy" href="/user/show/3357765-jimmy">Jimmy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 0811201171" href="/book/show/27275462-death-in-midsummer-and-other-stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3357765-jimmy?shelf=mishima">mishima</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3357765-jimmy?shelf=stories">stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3292505016" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2709189496911707589">The story &quot;Patriotism&quot; knocks me out every time I read it. It is in third-person point of view, but we see it through the eyes of Reiko, the wife of the lieutenant who is about to commit seppuku. She will follow him in basically the same fashion. The entire act is done with such love and sexual tension. It might as well have been a sex scene. <br/><br/>What I wonder about the most is what went on in the mind of Mishima as he wrote this. Was he already contemplating his own ritualistic suicide? Was it alwa</span>
  <span id="freeText2709189496911707589" style="display:none">The story "Patriotism" knocks me out every time I read it. It is in third-person point of view, but we see it through the eyes of Reiko, the wife of the lieutenant who is about to commit seppuku. She will follow him in basically the same fashion. The entire act is done with such love and sexual tension. It might as well have been a sex scene. <br /><br />What I wonder about the most is what went on in the mind of Mishima as he wrote this. Was he already contemplating his own ritualistic suicide? Was it always his plan? <br /><br />I also wonder if there has ever been another author who described a suicide in such detail and then died the same way. I can't think of any. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2709189496911707589" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


