<div id="review_317477674" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/317477674" />
    <a title="Rin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7997551-rin"><img alt="Rin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1343912880p2/7997551.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/317477674?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rin" href="/user/show/7997551-rin">Rin</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer317477674" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer628340648591602919">Yukio Mishima is one of the best modern writers of Japan.This book is one of his famous works, no doubt. Right. Stories in this book are really beautiful, enchanting , and poetic. His stories nail on tiny details to paint the overall pictures. There are tons of symbols (culture, politics etc) and implications behind the surface.Some of his stories are quite bitter about the modernization and Westernization of Japanese culture,the trying-too-hard effort to copy Western /American lifestyles of Jap</span>
  <span id="freeText628340648591602919" style="display:none">Yukio Mishima is one of the best modern writers of Japan.This book is one of his famous works, no doubt. Right. Stories in this book are really beautiful, enchanting , and poetic. His stories nail on tiny details to paint the overall pictures. There are tons of symbols (culture, politics etc) and implications behind the surface.Some of his stories are quite bitter about the modernization and Westernization of Japanese culture,the trying-too-hard effort to copy Western /American lifestyles of Japanese society during years after being losing World War II. Beside, the stories lightly display the rotting morale values among Japanese society under Yukio's viewpoint, and his indicated love for The Imperial.If you do a little more research on Yukio's life and his seppuku suicide, the indications seem more consistent and understandable. <br /><br />His stories are really subtle, well, at least for me-I'm not a really keen reader. Really subtle. Big message. The stories lure readers to big wonder at the very last sentences of those stories. Well, I chose not to star the book because the stars about 'like or not like it', and if I chose stars based on my preference and taste, my stars won't do the justice for the book. Meanwhile, the book is not for my taste , at least, right now. Well, perhaps, I will enjoy the book much more years later, in different time. </span>
  <a data-text-id="628340648591602919" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


