        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2823978980?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gillyz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gillyz" href="/user/show/71260076-gillyz">Gillyz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71260076-gillyz?shelf=tales-and-poems">tales-and-poems</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71260076-gillyz?shelf=curiosity">curiosity</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2823978980" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4248430491209810211">The English translation is sometimes weird - but you can still get the sense of it. I wish I could read Japanese. <br/><br/>I enjoyed all tales, but I loved only two of them: <br/><br/>Death in midsummer: a disaster in the beach that led to death of three family members shakes the structure of a couple&apos;s marriage and life. The development of the story gives you a heavy feeling of grief, guilt, and despair. Little by little it turns to a distant memory, till the couple decides to spend a few days on the same beach w</span>
  <span id="freeText4248430491209810211" style="display:none">The English translation is sometimes weird - but you can still get the sense of it. I wish I could read Japanese. <br /><br />I enjoyed all tales, but I loved only two of them: <br /><br />Death in midsummer: a disaster in the beach that led to death of three family members shakes the structure of a couple's marriage and life. The development of the story gives you a heavy feeling of grief, guilt, and despair. Little by little it turns to a distant memory, till the couple decides to spend a few days on the same beach where they had lost their loved ones.<br /><br />Patriotism (a better translation would be "concern for one's country"): A couple commits seppuku (ritual suicide) in the wake of the Ni Ni Roku Incident. This detailed and exciting story is one of those that makes me realize how the Japanese mentality, culture and traditions differ from western's. It gave me chills!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4248430491209810211" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


